<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <!-- The above 3 meta tags *must* come first in the head; any other head content must come *after* these tags -->
  <title>Bootstrap 101 Template</title>

  <!-- Bootstrap -->
  <link href="css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">

  <!-- HTML5 shim and Respond.js for IE8 support of HTML5 elements and media queries -->
  <!-- WARNING: Respond.js doesn't work if you view the page via file:// -->
  <!--[if lt IE 9]>
  <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/html5shiv/3.7.2/html5shiv.min.js"></script>
  <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/respond/1.4.2/respond.min.js"></script>
  <![endif]-->
</head>

<body>

<div class="jumbotron" id="welcome-jumbo">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="welcome-container">
      <h1 class="welcome-text">RoadTripper</h1>
      <p class="welcome-text">Helping you discover the best your road trip has to offer</p>
      <p class="welcome-button"><a class="btn btn-default btn-lg" href="<%= login_path %>" role="button">Hit the Road!</a></p>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-down" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- Example row of columns -->
  <div class="row index-guides">
    <div class="col-md-4">
      <h2 class="index-guide">Why</h2>
      <p class="index-text">Because road trips are fun! Planning road trips isn't always as easy, though. We're travel enthusiasts ourselves and we know how much effort goes into planning the perfect trip. Connecting road trippers with the best routes to make the most of their trips is why we do what we do. </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
      <h2 class="index-guide">What</h2>
      <p class="index-text">We help you plan the perfect road trip. We all know the big cities have tons to offer, and easy pickings on road trips, but what about stops you never would have thought of? We can give you a cool new suggestion based on where you are and where you're going, and we'll even map out the fastest route so you can make the most of your time. </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
      <h2 class="index-guide">How</h2>
      <p class="index-text">We've done our research, and we use our findings to help you find something interesting to explore based on where you're going. We're big fans of wandering off the beaten path and discovering hidden gems, so login, tell us about your trip, and will give you something new and fresh to check out. </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div> <!-- /container -->

<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12">
      <h2 class="index-guide">Planning a trip of your own?</h2>
      <p class="welcome-button"><a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="<%= login_path %>" role="button">Hit the Road!</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12">
      <hr>

      <footer>
        <p>&copy; RoadTripper 2015</p>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<!-- jQuery (necessary for Bootstrap's JavaScript plugins) -->
<script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.11.3/jquery.min.js"></script>
<!-- Include all compiled plugins (below), or include individual files as needed -->
<script src="js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
